<TEXT>
 The South Korean automaker will offer four cars, two models each of the Excel and the Sonata, for the 1990 model year. The Sonata features a new 3-liter, V-6 engine with a five-speed standard transmission. The upgraded Sonata GLS adds power door locks and windows, cruise control and other items. Leather upholstery is optional. The subcompact Excel has been redesigned inside and out with a more powerful engine. The GL version upgrades the trim level of the standard Excel.
